org.nasdanika.codegen.ecore.web.ui.model

Interface EReferenceConfiguration

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CDOObject, CDOWithID, EModelElementConfiguration, ENamedElementConfiguration, EObject, EStructuralFeatureConfiguration, ETypedElementConfiguration, Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EReferenceConfigurationImpl

    public interface EReferenceConfiguration
extends EStructuralFeatureConfiguration

    A representation of the model object ‘EReference Configuration’.

    The following features are supported:

    • Choices Selector
    • View
    • View Features
    • Element Types
    • Type Column
    See Also:
    ModelPackage.getEReferenceConfiguration()

      • getViewFeatures

        String getViewFeatures()

        Returns the value of the ‘View Features’ attribute. One of the following

        • A space-separated list of feature names.
        • A YAML document list of feature names or mappings of feature name to feature configuration definition, which may include:
          • visible - JXPath expression. If this expression evaluates to true (compared with Boolean.TRUE), then the feature is included in the list.
          • align - left, center, or right. Defaults to right for numbers, center for dates and booleans and left for other types.
          • width - if this key maps to a number, then the number is used for all device sizes. Otherwise is shall map to a map of device-size to number mappings.

        Example:

        - name:
     align: right
     width: 5
- age:
    aligh: left
    width:
         xs: 3        
 - ssn
        Returns:
        the value of the ‘View Features’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setViewFeatures(String), ModelPackage.getEReferenceConfiguration_ViewFeatures()

      • getElementTypes

        String getElementTypes()

        Returns the value of the ‘Element Types’ attribute. Specifies EClass-es of elements which can be instantiated and set/added to the reference.
        The list of element types shall be space-separated. Elements shall be in the following format: <eclass name>[@<epackage ns uri>]. EPackage namespace URI part can be omitted if the class is in the same package with the feature’s declaring EClass.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Element Types’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setElementTypes(String), ModelPackage.getEReferenceConfiguration_ElementTypes()

      • getTypeColumn

        String getTypeColumn()

        Returns the value of the ‘Type Column’ attribute. If not blank, indicates that the table listing reference elements shall display elements type in a type column. The value of this attribute is a pattern which is interpolated with the following tokens:

        • icon - Element icon.
        • eclass-icon - Element type icon.
        • eclass-label - Element type label.
        • documentation-icon - Documentation icon or blank string if there is no documentation.

        This attribute is useful for references containing elements of different types.

        Returns:
        the value of the ‘Type Column’ attribute.
        See Also:
        setTypeColumn(String), ModelPackage.getEReferenceConfiguration_TypeColumn()
